org.certificateservices.custom.c2x.ieee1609dot2.validator

Interface DefaultSSPLookup

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmptyDefaultSSPLookup

    public interface DefaultSSPLookup
    Interface for implementations to lookup Default SSP Data for a specific SSP. This is used for validating certificate where ssp data or ssp range data is omitted which means default data should be used which is up to each SSP Owner to define.

      • getDefaultSSP

        ServiceSpecificPermissions getDefaultSSP(Psid psid)
        Method to return default ServiceSpecificPermissions for a specific Psid. If no default value exist should null be returned.
        Parameters:
        psid - the PSID to lookup default ssp range for.
        Returns:
